<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-55-0464 </DOCNO><TEXT>Wood waste and municipal solid waste are important potential sources ofenergy in B.C. The forest industry has been using waste as a fuel formany years and today wood waste makes up approximately 21 percent ofthe total energy used in the province. Wood waste appears to have greatpotential as an energy resource not only for the forest industry butfor other industrial consumers as well. The Provincial government hasbeen actively encouraging the use of wastes as an energy resource througha number of projects. This paper discusses the resource base availablein British Columbia and provides preliminary data from some of the demonstrationprojects currently under way. 3 figs.</TEXT></DOC>